			shape: "gear"
			size: 1.5d
			tasks: [{
				id: "6A6B000ACCDD0001"
				item: "gtceu:mv_machine_hull"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "MV Machine Hull"
			x: -2.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5A5B000ACCDD000A"]
			description: ["The MV Electric Motor is wound with finer copper wire than its LV counterpart, providing higher rotation frequency at medium voltage. It is a prerequisite for the MV Piston, MV Robot Arm, MV Conveyor, and all MV machines that follow. Craft several before beginning the MV machine floor — the component demand for a full MV suite exceeds LV by a significant margin, and every delay in motor production cascades into delays in every downstream machine."]
			id: "5A5B000BCCDD000B"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "7A7B000BCCDD0001"
				item: "kubejs:coin"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "6A6B000BCCDD0001"
				item: "gtceu:mv_electric_motor"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "MV Motor"
			x: 0.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5A5B000BCCDD000B"]
			description: ["The MV Electrolyzer decomposes chemical compounds into their constituent elements using electrical current. At MV tier it handles Alumina into Aluminium and Oxygen, Chromite into Chrome and Iron Oxide, Water into Hydrogen and Oxygen, and dozens of other industrial reactions. Chrome — required for both Kanthal Alloy and Stainless Steel — is most efficiently produced through Chromite ore electrolysis. The MV Electrolyzer is the gateway to GTCEu's chemical processing tree, which runs in parallel with ore processing from this tier onward and scales with every tier above."]
			id: "5A5B000CCCDD000C"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "7A7B000CCCDD0001"
				item: "kubejs:coin"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "6A6B000CCCDD0001"
				item: "gtceu:mv_electrolyzer"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "MV Electrolyzer"
			x: 2.0d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5A5B000BCCDD000B"]
			description: ["The MV Chemical Reactor handles fluid-reagent chemistry at medium voltage — Sulfuric Acid from Sulfur and Water, Hydrochloric Acid, Sodium Persulfate for PCB etching, and the Chromite leaching chain. Unlike the LV reactor it accepts simultaneous fluid and solid inputs with wider throughput limits. Set it producing Sulfuric Acid continuously from the start — it is consumed by Aluminium processing, Platinum group chemistry, and nearly every industrial leaching reaction that follows in HV and beyond."]
			id: "5A5B000DCCDD000D"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "7A7B000DCCDD0001"
				item: "kubejs:coin"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "6A6B000DCCDD0001"
				item: "gtceu:mv_chemical_reactor"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "MV Chemical Reactor"
			x: 2.0d
			y: 2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: [
				"5A5B000CCCDD000C"
				"5A5B000BCCDD000B"
			]
			description: ["Kanthal is an iron-chromium-aluminium alloy that forms the heating element of high-temperature EBF coil blocks. Process Chromite Ore through the Macerator to obtain Chromite Dust, then electrolyze it to Chrome Ingot. Alloy Iron, Chrome, and Aluminium in the Alloy Smelter to form Kanthal Ingots — draw through the Wiremill to produce Kanthal Double Wire, then assemble four wire units into Kanthal Coil Blocks. Four blocks replace the Cupronickel ring of your EBF and raise its operating temperature to 2700K."]
			id: "5A5B000ECCDD000E"
			rewards: [{
				count: 4
				id: "7A7B000ECCDD0001"
				item: "kubejs:coin"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [
				{
